                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, July 17: The countrys foreign exchange reserves rose to $279.42 billion for the week ended July 9, up around $1.16 billion over the previous week, backed by a healthy jump in foreign currency assets (FCA). During the week, FCAs grew $1.13 billion to $253.26 billion from $252.12 billion a week ago, the RBI said.                             
	 New Delhi, July 17: Mahindra amp; Mahindra plans to hire over 250 people by 2015 for its pre-owned vehicle business even as it gears up to meet the target of selling one lakh units every year by 2014.                             
	 Mumbai, July 17: Development Credit Bank (DCB) has cut down its losses to Rs 2.9 crore in the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 35.3 crore in the year-ago period, backed by an ongoing restructuring plan.                                                                                                                          
